      <content><![CDATA[<p>You want to run a website with OpenCms. So you need to set up a webserver and install OpenCms on it. Here you learn about the hardware and software requirements for running OpenCms in the web. In further topics you can find out</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="%(link0)">How to configure Apache as webserver for OpenCms</a></li>
<li><a href="%(link1)">How to configure Tomcat as servlet container connected to the Apache webserver</a></li>
<li><a href="%(link2)">How to install and configure OpenCms for running on your Tomcat-Apache-combo</a></li>
<li><a href="%(link3)">How to make your OpenCms installation secure</a></li>
</ul>
<p>You have to look somewhere else if</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="%(link4)">You want to install OpenCms only locally on your computer.</a></li>
</ul>]]></content>
